Rating: 4
Really quite excellent! I had not read the reviews before making this and I did not EXPECT the cheese to melt--it is meant to enhance the flavor and texture of the dish and add another taste dimension, which it does very nicely. It's not meant to make a cheese sauce or gratin dish. The broccoli should be al dente with the cheese just warmed and softened. It was delicious this way! I used grated romano and served with spicy grilled salmon from this website with garlic and olive oil couscous. Exceptional meal and a definite four forks!

