This was excellent, quick, and easy to prepare. I cut the recipe in half, used a lid with steam vent while cooking the broccoli, substituted dry Jack for the Parmesan cheese, and added a sprinkling of sesame seeds. I quickly sprinkled on the cheese, tossed to coat, and served. The cheese melted to perfection. We were delighted with the color of the al dente broccoli and with the freshness of the taste, thanks to the lemon zest. We'll have this many more times.

